<p>Cerebrolysin splits the medical world along geographic lines. In Russia, China, and much of Europe, it's a mainstream treatment for stroke and dementia. In the United States, most neurologists have never heard of it.</p>

<p>This disconnect isn't because the research doesn't exist. It's because the regulatory and commercial environment makes it invisible to American medicine.</p>

<div class="d">
