<!-- ========== COMPOUND OVERVIEW ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>Cerebrolysin at a Glance</h2>

<div class="cd cb">
  <div class="tg">Compound Profile</div>
  <h3>Cerebrolysin (Porcine Brain Peptide Complex)</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Composition:</strong> ~25% low-molecular-weight peptides + ~75% free amino acids &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Source:</strong> Purified porcine (pig) brain tissue &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Manufacturer:</strong> EVER Neuro Pharma (Austria) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Mechanism:</strong> Mimics BDNF, NGF, GDNF activity &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Routes:</strong> IM (up to 5 mL) or IV (above 5 mL) &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>FDA Status:</strong> Not submitted for approval &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Approved in:</strong> 40+ countries including Russia, China, Austria, Germany</p>
</div>

<p>Cerebrolysin is a <a href="/articles/what-are-peptides-beginners-guide">peptide preparation</a> derived from purified porcine brain tissue. It's manufactured through a standardized enzymatic process that breaks down brain proteins into small peptides and free amino acids.</p>

<p>The peptide fraction (below 10 kDa) provides the biological activity. These peptides mimic naturally occurring neurotrophic factors, the proteins your brain uses to grow, maintain, and repair neurons.</p>

<p>Think of it as a cocktail of brain-derived signaling molecules, not a single compound with a single target. For a deeper compound profile, visit <a href="https://peptidearc.com">PeptideArc</a>.</p>

